headline: Eastman Chemical forecasts quarterly profit below expectations, cuts spending amid market uncertainty
summary: The chemical industry faces weak demand and high input costs, particularly in Europe, where a challenging regulatory environment has prompted companies to rethink their strategies.  Trump's erratic trade policies further add to uncertainty for the industry.  The company now expects second-quarter adjusted profit to be between $1.70 and $1.90 per share, below Wall Street expectations of $2.18 per share, according to data compiled by LSEG.
